               <n2016:NUTS CODE="NO"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The objective of the qualification scheme is to qualify service providers for participation in coming competitions for the purchase of buses. The scheme also comprises associated maintenance services. The scheme concerns both tender offers in tender competitions that Unibuss shall participate in, and the need for supplementary buses on existing contracts. The scheme also applies for the replacement of tour coaches and express buses and supplementary procurement of these.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <DATE_START>2018-01-24</DATE_START>
               <DATE_END>2020-01-24</DATE_END>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <LEFTI>
            <QUALIFICATION>
               <CONDITIONS>
                  <P>Requirement:</P>
                  <P>The tenderer must have their affairs in order with respect to the payment of tax, employer contribution and value added tax (VAT).</P>
                  <P>Documentation requirement:</P>
                  <P>Tax Certificate not older than 6 months, calculated from the date of application to participate in the scheme. A Tax Certificate is defined as:</P>
                  <P>For Norwegian tenderers:</P>
                  <P>— tax and VAT certificate issued by the tax office via Altinn.</P>
                  <P>For foreign tenderers:</P>
                  <P>— foreign tenderers must submit equivalent certificates from their own country that show that they have an arrangement for the payment of taxes and duties. If the authorities in the relevant country do not issue these certificates, the tenderer should submit a statement which states that all taxes and duties have been paid. The statement shall be approved and signed by the tenderer's Financial Director/person responsible for finance.</P>
               </CONDITIONS>
            </QUALIFICATION>
            <QUALIFICATION>
               <CONDITIONS>
                  <P>Requirement:</P>
                  <P>Tenderers shall be a legally established company.</P>
                  <P>Documentation requirement:</P>
                  <P>Norwegian tenderers:</P>
                  <P>— Company Registration Certificate.</P>
                  <P>Foreign tenderers:</P>
                  <P>— Confirmation that the tenderer is registered in a trade register or company register in accordance with the law in the country where the tenderer is established.</P>
               </CONDITIONS>
            </QUALIFICATION>
            <QUALIFICATION>
               <CONDITIONS>
                  <P>Requirement:</P>
                  <P>Tenderer shall comply with the Contracting Authority's ethical requirements for suppliers.</P>
                  <P>Documentation requirement:</P>
                  <P>Signed self-declaration that the Tenderer is familiar with and will maintain the Contracting Authority’s ethical requirements for suppliers, cf. Annex 2: Self-declaration, ethical Requirements for Suppliers.</P>
               </CONDITIONS>
            </QUALIFICATION>
            <QUALIFICATION>
               <CONDITIONS>
                  <P>Requirement:</P>
                  <P>The tenderer must have sufficient financial strength to carry out assignments under the qualification scheme.</P>
                  <P>Documentation requirement:</P>
                  <P>The tenderer's Annual Financial Statement including the auditor's report for the last 2 years.</P>
                  <P>A credit rating from an independent credit rating company must also be enclosed.</P>
               </CONDITIONS>
            </QUALIFICATION>
            <QUALIFICATION>
               <CONDITIONS>
                  <P>Requirement:</P>
                  <P>The tenderer must have adequate implementation ability.</P>
                  <P>Documentation requirement:</P>
                  <P>A short, general description of the company shall be given, including:</P>
                  <P>— an overview of the company’s history, organisation and ownership, as well as a description of the current business activities,</P>
                  <P>— a brief description of the overall quality assurance system that the tenderer will use for the execution of the contract,</P>
                  <P>— a description shall be given of the environmental management system the tenderer will use for the execution of the contract.</P>
                  <P>— a description shall be given of the company's internal anti-corruption initiatives,</P>
                  <P>— a description shall be given of the company's systems and/or routines for complying with laws, rules and ethically accountable business conduct.</P>
               </CONDITIONS>
            </QUALIFICATION>
            <QUALIFICATION>
               <CONDITIONS>
                  <P>Requirement:</P>
                  <P>The tenderer shall have good experience from equivalent assignments.</P>
                  <P>Documentation requirement:</P>
                  <P>The tenderer shall submit a list of relevant assignments with a description in accordance with the points below:</P>
                  <P>— a brief description of the assignment,</P>
                  <P>— time of execution,</P>
                  <P>— scope of the assignment in monetary amount,</P>
                  <P>— name, and telephone number of the reference person at the Contracting Authority.</P>
                  <P>The Contracting Authority must have the possibility to contact the contact persons who are listed.</P>
               </CONDITIONS>
            </QUALIFICATION>
         </LEFTI>
